I"Â<p>Hereâ€™s a simple Thai Red Curry recipe for two, or one if youâ€™re hungry! Itâ€™s hot, sweet and very quick and easy to make. The most imoprtant ingredient is the red thai paste. I buy mine but you can make some - hereâ€™s a couple of great recipes if you want to give it a go.</p>

<p><a target="_blank" href="https://www.eatingthaifood.com/thai-red-curry-paste-recipe/" class="btn badge-primary"> Red Paste Recipes â†’</a></p>

<h1 id="ingredients">Ingredients</h1>

<ul>
  <li>Red Thai Paste (2 tablesppons)</li>
  <li>Coconut Milk (400ml / 1 can)</li>
  <li>A few Lime Leaves or 1 Lime</li>
  <li>1 Red Bell Pepper</li>
  <li>Rice (any type works)</li>
  <li>Soy Sauce (2 teaspoons)</li>
  <li>2 Chicken Breasts</li>
</ul>

<h1 id="method">Method</h1>

<ol>
  <li>Heat a work or a large non stick pan on high heat.</li>
  <li>With the pan hot, add 100g (quarter can) or the coconut milk. This will spatter.</li>
  <li>After the milk has warmed a couple of minutes, add two tablespoons of Red Thai Paste and mix.</li>
  <li>Add the chicken to the mix and ensure the chicken is cooked.</li>
  <li>Chop the bell peppers and add to the curry.</li>
  <li>Drop the temperature to a steady simmer and add the remainder of the coconut milk ~ 300ml and stir.</li>
  <li>Add the lime leaves or squeeze half a limes juice into the curry, then add the soy sauce (2 tbsp).</li>
  <li>Taste the curry, seasoning and ensuring itâ€™s hot enough.</li>
  <li>Serve with rice and a decorative lime wedge.</li>
</ol>

<p>I took this recipe from this YouTube video: <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Bduxpd1_EVA">Kravings Red Thai Curry</a></p>

